   <div class=\"mw-body-content\" id=\"siteNotice\">\n    <!-- CentralNotice -->\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n   </div>\n   <h1 class=\"firstHeading\" id=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">\n    Felix of Trier\n   </h1>\n   <div class=\"mw-body-content\" id=\"bodyContent\">\n    <div class=\"noprint\" id=\"siteSub\">\n     From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\n    </div>\n    <div id=\"contentSub\">\n    </div>\n    <div id=\"contentSub2\">\n    </div>\n    <div id=\"jump-to-nav\">\n    </div>\n    <a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">\n     Jump to navigation\n    </a>\n    <a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#searchInput\">\n     Jump to search\n    </a>\n    <div class=\"mw-content-ltr\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\">\n     <div class=\"mw-parser-output\">\n      <div class=\"thumb tright\">\n       <div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\">\n        <a class=\"image\" href=\"/wiki/File:TabulaEpiscoporumTrevirensium.jpg\">\n         <img alt=\"\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-height=\"2208\" data-file-width=\"2005\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"242\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/TabulaEpiscoporumTrevirensium.jpg/220px-TabulaEpiscoporumTrevirensium.jpg\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/TabulaEpiscoporumTrevirensium.jpg/330px-TabulaEpiscoporumTrevirensium.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/TabulaEpiscoporumTrevirensium.jpg/440px-TabulaEpiscoporumTrevirensium.jpg 2x\" width=\"220\"/>\n        </a>\n        <div class=\"thumbcaption\">\n         <div class=\"magnify\">\n          <a class=\"internal\" href=\"/wiki/File:TabulaEpiscoporumTrevirensium.jpg\" title=\"Enlarge\">\n          </a>\n         </div>\n         Tabula Episcoporum Trevirensium\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <p>\n       <b>\n        Felix of Trier\n       </b>\n       (\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Floruit\" title=\"Floruit\">\n        fl\n       </a>\n       . c. 386\u2013399) was\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Bishop_of_Trier\" title=\"Bishop of Trier\">\n        bishop of Trier\n       </a>\n       from around 386 to 398.\n       <sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-1\">\n        <a href=\"#cite_note-1\">\n         [1]\n        </a>\n       </sup>\n       <sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-2\">\n        <a href=\"#cite_note-2\">\n         [2]\n        </a>\n       </sup>\n       <sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-3\">\n        <a href=\"#cite_note-3\">\n         [3]\n        </a>\n       </sup>\n      </p>\n      <p>\n       His episcopate was marked by the trial of\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Priscillian\" title=\"Priscillian\">\n        Priscillian\n       </a>\n       and his followers and their subsequent execution for heresy and witchcraft, which can be seen as the first inquisitorial action in the Church.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n       The death sentences against Priscillian and his followers, despite the vigorous opposition of many bishops of the West, including celebrities such as\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Martin_of_Tours\" title=\"Martin of Tours\">\n        Martin of Tours\n       </a>\n       and\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Ambrose_of_Milan\" title=\"Ambrose of Milan\">\n        Ambrose of Milan\n       </a>\n       , were to have bitter consequences for Felix:\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Pope_Siricius\" title=\"Pope Siricius\">\n        Pope Siricius\n       </a>\n       , Martin of Tours, Ambrose of Milan and other bishops broke off fellowship with all the bishops who took part in the trial of Priscillian. Felix was accused of not having campaigned vigorously enough against the verdict.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n       At a Synod of Bishops in 398 at Turin all bishops were readmitted to communion with\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Rome\" title=\"Rome\">\n        Rome\n       </a>\n       , provided that they undertook to have nothing to do with Felix, who was thus largely isolated. In 398 he renounced his bishopric.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n       Felix returned the relics of\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Paulinus_of_Trier\" title=\"Paulinus of Trier\">\n        Paulinus of Trier\n       </a>\n       from\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Phrygia\" title=\"Phrygia\">\n        Phrygia\n       </a>\n       to\n       <a href=\"/wiki/Trier\" title=\"Trier\">\n        Trier\n       </a>\n       and built a church to house them which is among the predecessors of the present\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/St._Paulinus%27_Church,_Trier\" title=\"St. Paulinus' Church, Trier\">\n        St. Paulinus' Church\n       </a>\n       , in the crypt of which he is buried.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n       His\n       <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Feast_day\" title=\"Feast day\">\n        feast day\n       </a>\n       is 26 March.\n       <sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">\n        [\n        <i>\n         <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\">\n          <span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (August 2017)\">\n           citation needed\n          </span>\n         </a>\n        </i>\n        ]\n       </sup>\n      </p>\n      <h2>\n       <span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">\n        References\n       </span>\n       <span class=\"mw-editsection\">\n        <span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">\n         [\n        </span>\n        <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Felix_of_Trier&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">\n         edit\n        </a>\n        <span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">\n         ]\n        </span>\n       </span>\n      </h2>\n      <div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n       <div class=\"mw-references-wrap\">\n        <ol class=\"references\">\n         <li id=\"cite_note-1\">\n          <span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">\n           <b>\n            <a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">\n             ^\n            </a>\n           </b>\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"reference-text\">\n           Ekkart Sauser\u00a0: Saints and Blessed in the Diocese of Trier 1987.\n          </span>\n         </li>\n         <li id=\"cite_note-2\">\n          <span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">\n           <b>\n            <a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">\n             ^\n            </a>\n           </b>\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"reference-text\">\n           <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/15042a.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">\n            Catholic Encyclopedia: Trier\n           </a>\n          </span>\n         </li>\n         <li id=\"cite_note-3\">\n          <span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">\n           <b>\n            <a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">\n             ^\n            </a>\n           </b>\n          </span>\n          <span class=\"reference-text\">\n           <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/trie0.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">\n            GCatholic: Diocese of Trier\n           </a>\n          </span>\n         </li>\n        </ol>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <table class=\"wikitable succession-box\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:95%;clear:both;\">\n       <tbody>\n        <tr>\n         <th colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-top: 5px solid #FABE60;\">\n          <a href=\"/wiki/Four_Marks_of_the_Church\" title=\"Four Marks of the Church\">\n           Titles of the Great Christian Church\n          </a>\n         </th>\n        </tr>\n        <tr style=\"text-align:center;\">\n         <td rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width:30%;\">\n          Preceded\u00a0by\n          <br/>\n          <span style=\"font-weight: bold\">\n           <a href=\"/wiki/Britto_of_Trier\" title=\"Britto of Trier\">\n            Britto of Trier\n           </a>\n          </span>\n         </td>\n         <td rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 40%; text-align: center;\">\n          <b>\n           <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/wiki/Bishop_of_Trier\" title=\"Bishop of Trier\">\n            Archbishop of Trier\n           </a>\n          </b>\n          <br/>\n          384 \u2013 398\n         </td>\n         <td rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\">\n          Succeeded\u00a0by\n          <br/>\n          <span style=\"font-weight: bold\">\n           <a href=\"/wiki/Mauritius_II_of_Trier\" title=\"Mauritius II of Trier\">\n            Mauritius II of Trier\n           </a>\n          </span>\n         </td>\n        </tr>\n       </tbody>\n      </table>\n      <!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1326\nCached time: 20200814001522\nCache expiry: 2592000\nDynamic content: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.124 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.197 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 539/1000000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 3334/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 823/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1043/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.050/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.56 MB/50 MB\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 1/400\n-->\n      <!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  174.715      1 -total\n 50.27%   87.837      1 Template:Citation_needed\n 33.01%   57.665      1 Template:Fix\n 23.58%   41.192      1 Template:Authority_control\n 22.14%   38.681      2 Template:Category_handler\n  8.52%   14.883      1 Template:Delink\n  7.15%   12.500      1 Template:S-bef\n  5.49%    9.584      1 Template:S-aft\n  4.53%    7.918      2 Template:Delink_question_hyphen-minus\n  4.29%    7.499      1 Template:S-ttl\n-->\n      <!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:51025665-0!canonical and timestamp 20200814001522 and revision id 847532925\n -->\n     </div>\n     <noscript>\n      <img alt=\"\" height=\"1\" src=\"//e